0.name: Asteroid-13
0.text:
This tape contains highly classified material and must not see the eyes of the public

A hidden bio-weapon testing facility has been discovered on the 13th Asteroid orbiting 56-vow

You have been tasked to find and extract what remains of  the weapons tested here

The facility has been destroyed but there are several rogue bio-weapons primed to kill anyone  and everyone in any way possible

Good luck

1.name: Infernis
1.text:
Tape 1, Infernis.

This is Captain Commander Cunningham.
I have decided to start recording our sites of research and the environments we find ourselves in.

Our current location is Infernis.
This fiery hellscape has done nothing but slow us down.
The seismic activity here is quite high so I'm not expecting to stay long.
Good thing.
The mineshafts are riddled with bugs and are very much preventing us from doing anything.

I rate this place a B=.
Cunningham, signing off.

2.name: Atlantica
2.text:
Tape 2, Atlantica.

This is Captain Cunningham.
Going to Atlantica wasn't something we had initially planned. It was purely our curiosity that has led us here.

As of now we have not yet encountered anything unnatural as the reports have said.
However, I do feel something is off about this place. It is pretty but something in me is telling me to leave.

So far I would rate this place a C.
However I might've changed my mind by the time we go.
Cunningham, signing off.

3.name: Acidir
3.text:
Tape 4, Acidir.
This is Captain Cunningham.

When we arrived here the crew seemed fine.
I use the term fine very loosely here.. They managed.

However I feel the longer we stay, the worse things seem to be getting.
I'm not sure if it's the air, the manor or the lakes of acid. But a few of us have already gone missing.

I rate Acidir an S.
Cunningham, signing off.

4.name: Etern
4.text:
Tape 3, Etern.

This is Captain Cunningham.
I have not been able to record much here and we will be leaving as soon as possible.

Our trip to Etern has been an absolute disaster. I’ve seen more nutcrackers searching for us than there are grains of sand in this desert.
We’ve lost many and I’m not keen on losing any more of us.

Etern gets an S+.
I highly discourage anyone from going here.
Cunningham, signing off.

5.name: Gratar
5.text:
Tape 5, Gratar.

This is Captain Commander Cunningham.
It hasn’t been long since we got here.
It already appears to be a nice fresh breath of air compared what we have been through before.

The view is undeniably.. Stunning and the local wildlife has yet to try and kill us.
We will be going in soon to have a chat with this AI before we take off again.

Thus far I rate Gratar a low C.
Cunningham, signing off.

6.name: Utril
6.text:
I really am cursed to live out my days recording with subpar recording devices.

This is professor Harrington and I have found myself to be on Utril.
The days may be darker than the nights yet it has a strange sense of beauty.
It is not a place I ever expected to visit.
The wildlife is unlike the usual, not very diverse.
Generally consistent of spore lizards and arachnids.
It was surprising to learn that it wasn't the spiders that were the aggressive ones here.
They were much more keen on posing for a picture.
Either way,
I'm needed back in the labs.
Professor Harrington, over and out.

7.name: Empra
7.text:
What is happiness?

Is it your dirty workplace?
Is it your filthy house?

Is it your crippling need for a therapist because you realised the universe is completely stacked against you and you will likely suffer the same fate as millions of others as the pressure of your worthless life becomes to much for the imagination of the mind leading to eventual damnination?


No!


Happiness is the one who sends you money!
Happiness is the one who created your job!
Happiness is the one who protects you!
Happiness is the Emperor!
And if you work hard enough,
You will be personally invited to live in his golden city!

Happiness is Empra!

Empra is happiness!

8.name: Motra
8.text:
Hi, it's harry with mighty mortor!
It's like a mortar but it's a mortor!
Mordor wouldn't have fallen with this mortar!

Regular defences don't work well.
People get their houses broken into all the time!
Burglars, thieves, your neighbors, nosy aunts, crazy exes, giants bees, nintendo, not even I will be able to break in with this thing in your backyard!

Normal mortars can only fire one shell at the time.
This thing can launch 30 of them within the blink of an eye!
Bet nobody expects that on their weather forecast!

You can put it in your backyard, put it on your car!
Attach it to your wallet, you'll spot it from afar!
You can even use it to collect water when you get deserted on an uninhabited island!

Mortors mortar, only 300.000 per piece!
But if you call now with in the next 20 minutes, we'll give you a second one absolutely free!

9.name: Gloom
9.text:
Are you in need of money?
Do you want a stable job?
Do you like safe and healthy work environments?

Come to gloom!

There are trees growing on trees.
And we need to get them all down.
Wood you help us with that?

Gloom Logging Company
Get logged in history

10.name: Oldred
10.text:
Hello employee.
You may not know me but.. I know you.
Since the death of your soulmate you have been taken by grief, you have felt like your existence is once again pointless.
You continuously put yourself in danger, inching closer and closer to the end each time.
Lets see if you have what it takes to survive, if you still appreciate the body that has been given to you.
In front of you there hangs a Decimator, an explosive device that will destroy everything in this room when the timer hits zero.
There also hangs another employee, you may know him as he has been in your crew for months, he will be the key to your freedom, All you need to do is remove the right wire with the knife you now posses.
But beware, if he dies by your hands, neither of you will make it out alive.
Live or die, make your choice.
